<img style="position: absolute !important; z-index: -1 !important; right: 1px !important; top: -20px !important; cursor: pointer !important; background-color: rgba(200, 200, 200, 0.3) !important; padding: 3px 5px 0 !important; margin: 0 !important;" onclick="document.location.href='http://translate.google.com/';" src="http://www.google.com/uds/css/small-logo.png" alt="" /></div>";i:2;s:0:"";i:3;s:0:"";i:4;s:8:"richtext";}s:13:"RadicalGiving";a:5:{i:0;s:13:"RadicalGiving";i:1;s:887:"<p>We should put a cap on our spending so that we can give more. Give to the church for ministry, give more to love offering, give toward mission trips, etc. </p>
<div id="-chrome-auto-translate-plugin-dialog" style="display: none; opacity: 1 !important; border-color: none !important; background: transparent !important; padding: 0 !important; margin: 0 !important; position: absolute !important; top: 0; left: 0; overflow: visible !important; z-index: 999999 !important; text-align: left !important;">
<img style="position: absolute !important; z-index: -1 !important; right: 1px !important; top: -20px !important; cursor: pointer !important; background-color: rgba(200, 200, 200, 0.3) !important; padding: 3px 5px 0 !important; margin: 0 !important;" onclick="document.location.href='http://translate.google.com/';" src="http://www.google.com/uds/css/small-logo.png" alt="" /></div>";i:2;s:0:"";i:3;s:0:"";i:4;s:8:"richtext";}s:11:"RadicalTime";a:5:{i:0;s:11:"RadicalTime";i:1;s:2247:"<p>Whether it's overseas for a short term missions trip or the soup kitchen downtown, we must go and be with people who aren't like us. Mt. Zion is planning two missions trips during 2011: Ecuador and Haiti.</p>
<h3>Ecuador</h3>
<p>Mt. Zion will be partnering with <a href="http://www.carycog.org/">Cary Church of God</a>&nbsp;as they prepare for an annual missions trip to Ecuador in mid-July. &nbsp;Please read the following information regarding the upcoming trip.</p>
<ul>
<li><a href="http://fb.me/DLHE2qN5">Audio From the February 7 Informational Meeting at Cary Church of God </a></li>
<li><a href="assets/files/Ecuador2011.pdf">Important Information/Dates Fact Sheet for Ecuador Mission Trip 2011</a></li>
<li><a href="http://www.carycog.org/ECUADOR.html">Cary Church of God's Information on Ecuador</a></li>
<li><a href="http://www.operationworld.org/country/ecua/owtext.html">Ecuador - Operation World</a></li>
</ul>
<h3>Haiti</h3>
<p>Northwest Haiti Christian Mission will be coordinating the trip to Haiti. &nbsp;The following information provides details on the trip including prices for anyone interested in attending.&nbsp;</p>
<ul>
<li><a href="http://www.nwhcm.org/misc/10TravelBookWeb.pdf">Team Member Pack - Northwest Haiti Christian Mission</a></li>
<li><a href="assets/files/HaitiMissionApplicationSubmission.pdf">Important Information Dates for Haiti Mission Trip 2012</a></li>
<li><a href="http://www.operationworld.org/country/hait/owtext.html">Haiti - Operation World</a></li>
</ul>
<div id="-chrome-auto-translate-plugin-dialog" style="display: none; opacity: 1 !important; border-color: none !important; background: transparent !important; padding: 0 !important; margin: 0 !important; position: absolute !important; top: 0; left: 0; overflow: visible !important; z-index: 999999 !important; text-align: left !important;">
<img style="position: absolute !important; z-index: -1 !important; right: 1px !important; top: -20px !important; cursor: pointer !important; background-color: rgba(200, 200, 200, 0.3) !important; padding: 3px 5px 0 !important; margin: 0 !important;" onclick="document.location.href='http://translate.google.com/';" src="http://www.google.com/uds/css/small-logo.png" alt="" /></div>";i:2;s:0:"";i:3;s:0:"";i:4;s:8:"richtext";}s:17:"RadicalCommitment";a:5:{i:0;s:17:"RadicalCommitment";i:1;s:1309:"<p>Be a part of a local church that is growing, making disciples and sending people out. Serve faithfully and pray fervently for it. And if you're not in a ministry, get into one. </p>
<h3>Project: Know Thy Neighbor</h3>
<p>Do you know your neighbors? &nbsp;Maybe there is someone you see on occasion 
that you might not know on a name basis, or some who lives near you whom
 you have never talked to. &nbsp;We have launched a new website to challenge 
you in your spiritual growth.&nbsp; For 
more information visit&nbsp; <a href="neighbors">Project: Know Thy Neighbor</a>.</p>
